The notifications dropdown is failing to refresh/toggle correctly because:

1. Content loads asynchronously via `socket.emit()` + `app.parseAndTranslate()`
2. After the HTML is rendered into `notifList.html(html)`, the dropdown menu's DOM has changed
3. The code never calls `bsDropdown.update()` to tell Bootstrap/Popper.js to recalculate positions
4. Popper.js still uses stale positioning calculations from before the content loaded
5. This causes visual glitches or dropdown positioning failures

---

